---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import DocsSubnav from '../../components/DocsSubnav.astro';
import MythicDivider from '../../components/MythicDivider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Docs · Quickstart"
  description="Install Zana, wire it into Claude Code, and run your first agent — in under five minutes."
>
  <DocsSubnav />

  <section class="container-zana py-16">
    <p class="ornament text-xs text-gold">— quickstart —</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-5xl text-forest md:text-6xl">First five minutes with Zana.</h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-moss leading-relaxed">
      Three steps to a working install: <strong>install</strong> the daemon,
      <strong>wire</strong> it into Claude Code, and <strong>spawn</strong> your
      first agent. Once it returns "PONG", you're ready for the recipes.
    </p>

    <article class="prose-zana mt-12 max-w-prose space-y-12">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">1. Install</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Node 20+ required. Clone and run the bundled installer.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="terminal" lang="bash">{`git clone https://github.com/grebmann1/zana.git
cd zana
bash scripts/install.sh

# or remote-pipe
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/grebmann1/zana/main/scripts/install.sh | bash`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">The installer handles npm install, runtime build, MCP server registration, and a guided <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana init wizard</code> for the workspace.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">2. Wire into Claude Code</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Register the marketplace and install the plugins.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="terminal" lang="bash">{`claude plugin marketplace add /absolute/path/to/zana
claude plugin install zana@zana-marketplace        # orchestrator + daemon-driven schedules
claude plugin install zana-loop@zana-marketplace   # lightweight /loop scheduling

# verify
claude mcp list | grep zana`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">Restart Claude Code. Type <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">/zana</code> and you'll see the orchestrator, autopilot, council, ticket, schedule, and loop families.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">3. Spawn your first agent</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Hello-world is one MCP call. <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">zana_oneshot_query</code> spawns a profile, waits for output, returns the answer.</p>
        <CodeBlock caption="claude code · MCP" lang="text">{`zana_oneshot_query({
  profileId: "researcher",
  prompt: "Reply with the single word: PONG",
  timeout: 90000
})
// → "PONG"`}</CodeBlock>
        <p class="mt-3 text-moss">If you see <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">"PONG"</code>, your install is good. This exact call is the first assertion in <code class="rounded bg-parchment px-1.5 py-0.5">scripts/qa/run-runtime.sh</code> (2/2 passing against real Claude).</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl text-forest">Where to next</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-moss">Pick the path that matches your work.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-moss">
          <li>· <a href="/docs/recipes/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">Recipes</a> — copy-paste end-to-end examples for tickets, schedules, autopilot, deliberation. Each one mirrored by a live Claude integration test.</li>
          <li>· <a href="/docs/concepts/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">Concepts</a> — deliberation, schedules, /loop vs daemon, runtime adapter.</li>
          <li>· <a href="/docs/cli/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry font-semibold">CLI reference</a> — drive Zana from the terminal (CI, scripts, ops).</li>
          <li>· <a href="/how-it-works/" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">How it works</a> — primitives in depth.</li>
          <li>· <a href="https://github.com/grebmann1/zana" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-forest hover:text-berry">GitHub repo</a> — issues, profiles, contributions.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <MythicDivider />
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
